  "notes": "Tigrinya (Tigrigna), spoken in Eritrea and Ethiopia. Ethiopic abugida. Retains pharyngeal /ħ/ (ሐ row) distinct from glottal /h/. Has ejective series and labiovelar extensions. Similar to Amharic but phonologically more conservative.",
